once again becoming the

00:02:14.900 --> 00:02:16.500
country we have always been.

00:02:16.500 --> 00:02:18.840
This is strictly logical, which
you cannot become, which

00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:22.770
you're not at present." What
do you say to this?

00:02:22.770 --> 00:02:23.670
STEPHEN COLBERT: Well,
I say to this.

00:02:23.670 --> 00:02:24.070
To Michael--

00:02:24.070 --> 00:02:26.370
ERIC SCHMIDT: This is the
hardest and toughest criticism

00:02:26.370 --> 00:02:27.950
of your title that
I have ever seen.

00:02:27.950 --> 00:02:28.151
STEPHEN COLBERT: OK.

00:02:28.151 --> 00:02:28.880
So Michael.

00:02:28.880 --> 00:02:32.120
"Michael." "Michael Jones."
Michael, the fool says in his

00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:33.480
heart there is no God.

00:02:33.480 --> 00:02:36.290
But by God, he means that thing
then which no greater

00:02:36.290 --> 00:02:38.320
thing can be conceived.

00:02:38.320 --> 00:02:41.920
But by conceiving of that
thing, he automatically

00:02:41.920 --> 00:02:45.720
defines God as whatever he
can greatest imagine.

00:02:45.720 --> 00:02:48.940
Therefore, God does exist
because he has imagined that

00:02:48.940 --> 00:02:51.520
thing which must be greater
in reality than in his

00:02:51.520 --> 00:02:53.120
imagination.

00:02:53.120 --> 00:02:55.640
ERIC SCHMIDT: I completely
agree.

00:02:55.640 --> 00:02:58.350
All right.

00:02:58.350 --> 00:02:59.910
STEPHEN COLBERT: Those of you
who are not familiar with

00:02:59.910 --> 00:03:02.860
