00:55:28.620 --> 00:55:31.280
A blog?

00:55:31.280 --> 00:55:31.750
Audio?

00:55:31.750 --> 00:55:32.410
Does a podcast.

00:55:32.410 --> 00:55:33.470
He does a great podcast.

00:55:33.470 --> 00:55:34.220
Yeah.

00:55:34.220 --> 00:55:34.880
What do you kids do?

00:55:34.880 --> 00:55:36.630
Your podcasts?

00:55:36.630 --> 00:55:37.700
He's a great guy.

00:55:37.700 --> 00:55:38.500
We're backstage.

00:55:38.500 --> 00:55:40.120
Somebody was on stage.

00:55:40.120 --> 00:55:43.150
And they were supposed to do
a very simple blackout.

00:55:43.150 --> 00:55:44.410
And a blackout is
a very short--

00:55:44.410 --> 00:55:45.080
it's got one joke.

00:55:45.080 --> 00:55:45.960
And then the lights go out.

00:55:45.960 --> 00:55:46.990
This is at Second City.

00:55:46.990 --> 00:55:48.720
It's a pace keeper
for the show.

00:55:48.720 --> 00:55:49.480
She goes out there.

00:55:49.480 --> 00:55:51.730
And the blackout is this.

00:55:51.730 --> 00:55:54.130
You're supposed to say, I'd like
to do a song for you now.

00:55:54.130 --> 00:55:56.900
Welcome to the No Exit Cafe.

00:55:56.900 --> 00:55:58.550
I'd like to do a song
for you right now, a

00:55:58.550 --> 00:56:00.220
song for the whales.

00:56:00.220 --> 00:56:03.960
And then you tune up your
guitar for a long time.

00:56:03.960 --> 00:56:05.800
This is a song for the whales.

00:56:05.800 --> 00:56:07.726
And then you go,
[MAKES WHALE SOUNDS].

00:56:10.500 --> 00:56:12.090
It's very simple.

00:56:12.090 --> 00:56:14.180
You do whistle and clicks
and everything.

00:56:14.180 --> 00:56:14.960
It's fine.

00:56:14.960 --> 00:56:18.170
Not a great laugh, but
it works every time.

00:56:18.170 --> 00:56:20.040
She goes out there to do it.

00:56:20.040 --> 00:56:22.360
I'd like to do a song
for you right now.

00:56:22.360 --> 00:56:23.910
I'd like to do a song
for you right now.

00:56:23.910 --> 00:56:25.950
